WEBVTT

00:22.172 --> 00:25.931
-Which would make you
final girl.

00:25.965 --> 00:27.344
-Well, then
who the hell are you?

00:27.379 --> 00:32.000
-Well, I'm obviously
the know-it-all horror guy.

00:32.034 --> 00:33.620
-Security breach.

00:33.655 --> 00:34.862
-No.
-Security breach.

00:34.896 --> 00:35.931
-You're not gonna
want to follow him.

00:35.965 --> 00:37.413
-Why?

00:38.655 --> 00:41.344
-I'm really surprised
she lasted this long.

00:43.344 --> 00:45.413
-I cannot stress this enough.

00:45.448 --> 00:47.586
Stay out.
-I wasn't even there.

00:47.620 --> 00:49.758
-Alarm.
-Run.

00:51.586 --> 00:52.724
-[Screams]

00:52.758 --> 00:54.827
-Don't mess with the bull, man.

00:54.862 --> 00:57.068
Or you'll get the horns.

00:57.103 --> 00:58.758
-Why would someone
give us a sequel?

00:58.793 --> 01:02.172
-What is important here is that
we are in a horror movie!

01:03.827 --> 01:05.379
-[Gasps]

01:05.413 --> 01:06.724
-You okay?

01:06.758 --> 01:09.068
-Thank you.
Not here, though.

01:09.103 --> 01:10.931
-She's not here.

01:10.965 --> 01:13.413
-I know.

01:13.448 --> 01:14.896
-What is it?

01:14.931 --> 01:17.689
-Just looks like he's
staring at me.

01:19.413 --> 01:21.344
-Oh, look at that picture.
It really captures his eyes.

01:21.379 --> 01:23.344
-Wait.
This is the video-store guy?

01:23.379 --> 01:26.103
-Yeah. There's, like,
not anybody here.

01:26.137 --> 01:28.310
[Clears throat]

01:28.344 --> 01:31.034
-What's up, Henry?
You piece of shit.

01:31.068 --> 01:32.482
-Holy shit, it's Good Guy.

01:32.517 --> 01:35.931
-Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Step away from Mr. Johnson.

01:35.965 --> 01:39.103
-It's okay.
Give the kiddies what they want.

01:39.137 --> 01:41.931
-That's the good guy.

01:41.965 --> 01:44.413
-Come on, swoop it.
Big swoop on the "K."

01:44.448 --> 01:45.827
Thank you.

01:45.862 --> 01:49.241
-Sweet. I got an autograph
from Good Guy's bodyguard.

01:49.275 --> 01:51.758
-Chad -- he has a twin?
-I've seen him before.

01:54.206 --> 01:57.172
-Why are we at
the video-store guy's funeral?

01:57.206 --> 01:59.413
-Mother.
-Ms. Kapowski.

02:00.758 --> 02:03.103
-Darling! Oh!

02:03.137 --> 02:04.931
-Do you know if there's
food here or not?

02:04.965 --> 02:08.172
-I believe there are
hors d'oeuvres, sir.

02:08.206 --> 02:10.586
-What the fuck's
an hors d'oeuvres?

02:10.620 --> 02:14.241
[Metal creaking]

02:14.275 --> 02:20.551
♪♪

02:20.586 --> 02:27.172
♪♪

02:31.344 --> 02:32.965
-Friends.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.068
Family.

02:35.103 --> 02:36.965
Countrymen.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.724
Welcome!

02:38.758 --> 02:43.241
First off, I'd like to give
a gigantic thank you to Adele,

02:43.275 --> 02:45.103
who just sang
that beautiful song.

02:45.137 --> 02:47.931
I'm just so glad
you could be here today.

02:47.965 --> 02:53.931
And to my friends and family,
who all made that happen.

02:53.965 --> 02:57.689
We're all rolling
in the deep together.

02:57.724 --> 03:01.379
It means so much to me
that you're here today.

03:01.413 --> 03:06.655
But it also means I've met
my tragic, yet likely heroic,

03:06.689 --> 03:09.896
but clearly untimely demise.

03:09.931 --> 03:11.379
Being beaten to death
against a tree

03:11.413 --> 03:13.448
while in my sleeping bag...

03:13.482 --> 03:17.931
...killed by a robot sent back
in time to stop the revolution.

03:17.965 --> 03:19.206
Leaving the oven on.

03:19.241 --> 03:20.827
Trapped under
a vending machine.

03:20.862 --> 03:22.344
...an ornate puzzle box.

03:22.379 --> 03:24.448
Great white sharks.
Choking on a chicken bone.

03:24.482 --> 03:26.379
Being separated
from my conjoined twin.

03:26.413 --> 03:29.379
Electrocution. A broken heart.
Buried alive.

03:29.413 --> 03:33.551
A hole punch through my face
by the Devil's Lake Impaler.

03:33.586 --> 03:36.448
Yeah, that's it.

03:36.482 --> 03:41.896
And now a hole in me
is a hole in all of you.

03:41.931 --> 03:44.448
And I know how hard this is.

03:46.137 --> 03:51.241
But you must keep on.

03:51.275 --> 03:55.793
You must live your lives.
You must persevere-ay.

03:58.034 --> 04:01.689
You must stay rad, my friends.

04:09.965 --> 04:12.965
♪♪

04:13.000 --> 04:14.965
-Time to go, I guess.

04:15.000 --> 04:16.655
-Let's get out of here.

04:16.689 --> 04:22.551
♪♪

04:22.586 --> 04:24.931
[Gas hissing]

04:24.965 --> 04:29.586
♪♪

04:29.620 --> 04:31.655
[People coughing]

04:31.689 --> 04:35.172
[Alarm beeping]

04:35.206 --> 04:37.379
-What the fuck is happening?

04:39.034 --> 04:41.965
-Where's the door?!

04:42.000 --> 04:44.586
-Pick him up.
Don't you dare drop him.

04:44.620 --> 04:46.655
-Bert, stay close to me!

04:46.689 --> 04:48.103
Stay close to me!

04:48.137 --> 04:49.275
-It's locked.

04:49.310 --> 04:51.172
-Where are his glasses?

04:51.206 --> 04:53.517
He can't see without
his glasses!

04:53.551 --> 05:00.413
♪♪

05:00.448 --> 05:03.517
-[Coughing]

05:03.551 --> 05:05.551
Hey!

05:05.586 --> 05:06.965
Hey!

05:07.000 --> 05:08.793
We're in here.

05:08.827 --> 05:16.655
♪♪

05:16.689 --> 05:24.448
♪♪

05:24.482 --> 05:26.827
[Glass shatters]

05:26.862 --> 05:36.551
♪♪

05:36.586 --> 05:46.344
♪♪

05:46.379 --> 05:47.931
-Mom?

05:47.965 --> 05:50.241
Are you okay?
-Are youokay?

05:50.275 --> 06:01.379
♪♪

06:01.413 --> 06:04.758
-[Deep voice] How would you
like to play a game?

06:04.793 --> 06:08.413
[Clears throat] I mean,
how'd you like to play a game?

06:08.448 --> 06:11.655
I used to play games all the
time by myself as a kid.

06:11.689 --> 06:13.275
This one's awesome.

06:13.310 --> 06:16.413
You all have been
specially chosen to take part

06:16.448 --> 06:18.689
in this fully
immersive experience

06:18.724 --> 06:20.620
like none other before.

06:20.655 --> 06:25.896
It's the ultimate
Rad Chad recommendation!

06:25.931 --> 06:27.758
[Deep voice] From beyond.

06:27.793 --> 06:31.655
But pay close attention.
It may just save your life.

06:31.689 --> 06:35.931
[Laughs maniacally]

06:35.965 --> 06:37.827
-I got you, K-Bear.

06:37.862 --> 06:41.689
-[Laughing maniacally]

06:48.310 --> 06:51.517
[Sighs]

06:51.551 --> 06:59.931
♪♪

06:59.965 --> 07:08.517
♪♪

07:08.551 --> 07:16.931
♪♪

07:16.965 --> 07:18.620
[Bell dings]

07:23.758 --> 07:25.689
[Bell dings]

07:25.724 --> 07:33.793
♪♪

07:33.827 --> 07:41.827
♪♪

07:41.862 --> 07:49.896
♪♪

07:49.931 --> 07:51.724
[Music thumping, twigs snapping]

07:51.758 --> 07:53.241
-What's that?

07:53.275 --> 07:55.620
-It's probably just
one of the Sure to Die girls

07:55.655 --> 07:58.551
making out
in the bushes again, Nancy.

07:58.586 --> 07:59.793
[Door opens]

07:59.827 --> 08:04.862
♪♪

08:04.896 --> 08:07.482
-Hey, Tony.

08:07.517 --> 08:09.275
-Got the wrong house again,
buddy.

08:09.310 --> 08:11.413
-Yeah, the New Year's Eve party
is next door,

08:11.448 --> 08:15.344
and the Sure to Die girls
are all ready for you.

08:15.379 --> 08:17.758
I'm sure.

08:17.793 --> 08:19.482
-If you're gonna
borrow our knives,

08:19.517 --> 08:23.103
please sharpen
before you return.

08:25.103 --> 08:26.827
[Knife slashes, girl screams]

08:26.862 --> 08:28.413
[Thud]

08:28.448 --> 08:34.655
♪♪

08:34.689 --> 08:36.586
-Is she okay?

08:36.620 --> 08:39.241
-Well, yeah.

08:39.275 --> 08:41.448
Laurie?

08:41.482 --> 08:46.068
Laurie, honey, you can get up.
There was some kind of mistake.

08:46.103 --> 08:49.000
-Oh, I don't think
that's a good idea, Ginny.

08:52.379 --> 08:56.275
-[Screams]

08:56.310 --> 08:59.310
-Yeah, that was a bad idea.

08:59.344 --> 09:02.965
-Guys, I think she's dead.
-She can't be dead.

09:03.000 --> 09:06.758
She was just studying, having
no fun, doing everything right.

09:10.965 --> 09:12.172
-Tony?

09:12.206 --> 09:14.448
-Sally, it might not be safe.

09:16.655 --> 09:20.068
-See? We are the final girls.

09:20.103 --> 09:21.793
Just look at
our androgynous faces,

09:21.827 --> 09:23.482
khaki pants,
and button-up shirts.

09:23.517 --> 09:29.379
Killers take us for granted.
They don't kill us.

09:29.413 --> 09:32.241
[Screaming]

09:32.275 --> 09:42.448
♪♪

09:42.482 --> 09:44.620
-[Panting]

09:47.000 --> 09:49.482
-Oh, hey, girls.

09:49.517 --> 09:51.206
We're all partying
super hard next door,

09:51.241 --> 09:53.000
and we just can't seem
to find our beer bongs.

09:53.034 --> 09:55.000
Do you happen to have any?

09:57.758 --> 09:59.620
-Uh, yeah.

09:59.655 --> 10:05.586
I think we have some
in storage in the basement.

10:05.620 --> 10:07.137
-What is a beer bong?

10:07.172 --> 10:08.827
You know, the Sure to Die girls
thought it'd be pointless

10:08.862 --> 10:12.000
to ask, but, hey,
it's almost the '90s.

10:12.034 --> 10:14.137
Maybe you guys have changed.

10:16.034 --> 10:17.689
[Whip, thud]

10:21.379 --> 10:23.344
-[Grunts]

10:31.241 --> 10:33.172
-Guys, I think we've
switched places

10:33.206 --> 10:35.724
with the Sure to Die girls.
That's crazy.

10:35.758 --> 10:38.103
They're sure to die.
What's next?

10:38.137 --> 10:40.413
Is a boy gonna be
the last one standing?

10:40.448 --> 10:42.413
[All laugh]

10:42.448 --> 10:43.827
-Good one.

10:43.862 --> 10:46.586
-We're no longer being rewarded
for being the outsiders.

10:46.620 --> 10:49.758
-For being smarter
than everyone in the room.

10:49.793 --> 10:51.655
-For being a bad-ass.

10:51.689 --> 10:55.448
-For avoiding sex till marriage.

10:55.482 --> 10:58.965
Okay, maybe not till marriage,
but I keep all my clothes on

10:59.000 --> 11:01.379
during sleepovers
and late-night parties.

11:01.413 --> 11:03.965
That's just common sense.
-Yeah, of course.

11:04.000 --> 11:05.517
-Yeah.
[Doorknob rattles]

11:05.551 --> 11:12.655
♪♪

11:12.689 --> 11:19.724
♪♪

11:19.758 --> 11:21.241
-Where'd he go?

11:22.620 --> 11:24.137
[All scream]

11:24.172 --> 11:27.448
He's gonna kill us all.
We need to do something.

11:27.482 --> 11:29.586
-Um, I can throw on
that ugly sweater

11:29.620 --> 11:32.862
I've been knitting and be
his mommy and shame him.

11:32.896 --> 11:35.724
"Bad Tony.
Bad Tony, killer guy."

11:35.758 --> 11:38.068
-I can stay awake for days.

11:38.103 --> 11:41.448
-I can go into hyper-sleep
until it all goes away.

11:41.482 --> 11:45.827
-Hey, you're the bad-ass.
Get it together.

11:45.862 --> 11:49.206
-Nothing makes sense anymore!

11:49.241 --> 11:51.241
[Doorknob rattling]

11:51.275 --> 12:02.896
♪♪

12:02.931 --> 12:04.206
-Hey.

12:04.241 --> 12:06.103
So, I didn't find
any beer bongs,

12:06.137 --> 12:08.206
but I did find this cool thing.

12:08.241 --> 12:10.793
-That's a turkey baster.

12:10.827 --> 12:14.758
-Ellen. "It's a turkey baster."
Are you mad at me?

12:16.413 --> 12:20.586
Oh, you should try this.
This is something different.

12:20.620 --> 12:22.068
-Okay. We have a plan.

12:22.103 --> 12:24.379
So, Tony is only
killing final girls.

12:24.413 --> 12:28.931
But what if we use her to
distract him while we get away?

12:28.965 --> 12:31.379
-Look at her.
Her knees are showing.

12:36.034 --> 12:38.379
-We'll make her one of us.

12:38.413 --> 12:50.827
♪♪

12:50.862 --> 12:54.172
[Glass shatters]

12:54.206 --> 12:57.172
-She still looks hot.
-So hot.

13:00.862 --> 13:02.068
-Oh, yeah.

13:02.103 --> 13:04.275
-That totally makes
a difference.

13:06.413 --> 13:09.793
-Okay, so, we're just gonna
leave you down here alone

13:09.827 --> 13:15.344
to, uh, do laundry
on New Year's Eve.

13:15.379 --> 13:17.172
-No problem.

13:29.689 --> 13:32.758
[Clock ticking]

13:32.793 --> 13:35.241
-Nothing is happening.

13:37.758 --> 13:39.517
-Where is he?

13:42.241 --> 13:45.827
-I have an idea.
-Of course you do.

13:45.862 --> 13:47.413
-It is almost midnight.

13:47.448 --> 13:53.689
And since the old rules
don't apply anymore, what if we,

13:53.724 --> 13:56.103
I don't know...

13:56.137 --> 13:59.172
party like we've never
partied before.

13:59.206 --> 14:01.103
-That's a good idea.

14:01.137 --> 14:04.275
[Record player crackles,
soft music plays]

14:04.310 --> 14:15.413
♪♪

14:15.448 --> 14:26.586
♪♪

14:26.620 --> 14:28.655
[Music grows harder]

14:28.689 --> 14:34.758
♪♪

14:34.793 --> 14:36.241
-[Roars]

14:36.275 --> 14:41.379
♪♪

14:41.413 --> 14:43.379
You're so pretty.

14:43.413 --> 14:51.551
♪♪

14:51.586 --> 14:54.241
Oh! Ow.

14:54.275 --> 14:56.793
This is fun.
[Slaps]

14:56.827 --> 14:59.068
[Door opens]

14:59.103 --> 15:00.965
We're trapped.

15:01.000 --> 15:02.758
[Chainsaw revs]

15:05.000 --> 15:06.965
-Hello, ladies.

15:07.000 --> 15:08.482
Laundry's done.

15:08.517 --> 15:10.344
Although I think I shrunk
that hideous wool skirt.

15:10.379 --> 15:13.379
Not that Laurie
needs it anymore. She's dead.

15:15.344 --> 15:16.931
Uh, you're welcome.
While you were finally

15:16.965 --> 15:18.724
discovering the joys
of personal pleasure,

15:18.758 --> 15:21.482
I saved you from that guy.

15:21.517 --> 15:24.586
Oh, crap.
-We didn't need your help.

15:24.620 --> 15:27.344
We've been doing fine
the past two decades,

15:27.379 --> 15:31.862
surviving, while girls
like you died tragically,

15:31.896 --> 15:34.034
walking alone in the woods,

15:34.068 --> 15:37.103
having sex after
a friend got murdered,

15:37.137 --> 15:41.620
partaking in a midnight snack
in the dark.

15:41.655 --> 15:43.137
Alone?

15:43.172 --> 15:45.551
[Chainsaw revs]
[Final girls scream]

15:45.586 --> 15:46.965
-Just kidding.

15:47.000 --> 15:50.724
You guys are right.
You don't need my help.

15:50.758 --> 15:52.655
-Found the beer bong, Buffy.

15:55.931 --> 15:57.793
-I did not mean to do that.

15:59.793 --> 16:01.206
-Leave us alone, you bitch.

16:01.241 --> 16:06.448
-You had a gun this whole time?

16:06.482 --> 16:08.586
-Look, I get it.

16:08.620 --> 16:11.551
You all survived because your
resilience and virginal vaginas

16:11.586 --> 16:14.517
gave you the power to fight
against the great male gaze.

16:14.551 --> 16:17.000
And it allowed you to be
that unlikely savior

16:17.034 --> 16:18.517
of your community.

16:18.551 --> 16:21.517
You proved their sexist theory
that being a good girl

16:21.551 --> 16:24.758
meant you were good enough
to survive.

16:24.793 --> 16:26.862
Catholic guilt, anybody?

16:26.896 --> 16:30.413
But also, let's be honest,
I mean, letting a lady survive

16:30.448 --> 16:33.413
allowed men to spend
the entire movie sexualizing

16:33.448 --> 16:36.862
and brutally murdering
every other woman in a film.

16:36.896 --> 16:38.724
Women like me.

16:38.758 --> 16:40.655
Who had sex.

16:40.689 --> 16:42.931
A lot of sex.

16:42.965 --> 16:45.379
And maybe didn't
love studying.

16:45.413 --> 16:46.862
-Yeah.

16:46.896 --> 16:48.517
-We had no chance.

16:48.551 --> 16:51.413
We were lucky
if they gave us pants.

16:51.448 --> 16:55.241
No, no, please. I'm --
I'm very okay wearing this.

16:55.275 --> 16:57.275
One, because
it's a cheerleading outfit,

16:57.310 --> 16:59.379
and cheerleading is a sport.

16:59.413 --> 17:03.517
And two, it is very practical
for kicking ass.

17:03.551 --> 17:05.655
But more importantly,
it does not indicate

17:05.689 --> 17:08.137
that I deserve to die.

17:08.172 --> 17:09.689
Isn't it time we all
come together

17:09.724 --> 17:13.241
and let women be women?

17:13.275 --> 17:15.379
Look at that gun.
How are you even holding that?

17:15.413 --> 17:17.896
-It's really heavy.
-Yeah.

17:17.931 --> 17:22.068
[Fireworks whistling,
clock chiming]

17:22.103 --> 17:24.517
-Happy New Year!

17:28.413 --> 17:31.931
♪♪

17:31.965 --> 17:34.275
Welcome to the '90s,
motherfucker.

17:37.241 --> 17:39.310
-That was pretty good.

17:42.551 --> 17:45.965
-[Distorted voice]
Horror fans are "so sick."

17:46.000 --> 17:50.275
That's what you say to us.
And, well, maybe you're right.

17:50.310 --> 17:52.586
Maybe weare sick.

17:52.620 --> 17:54.620
Sick of the pretension.

17:54.655 --> 17:56.758
Sick of the world
looking down on us

17:56.793 --> 17:59.310
because we don't dare turn away
from the violent,

17:59.344 --> 18:02.137
the sinister, the macabre.

18:02.172 --> 18:05.862
Oh, yes. We are sick.

18:05.896 --> 18:08.379
Sick of you judging us.

18:08.413 --> 18:13.344
And now a sickness
lies within you, as well.

18:13.379 --> 18:16.448
There's a poison
coursing through your veins,

18:16.482 --> 18:20.551
giving you mere minutes to put
what you learned from the film

18:20.586 --> 18:22.413
to the ultimate test.

18:22.448 --> 18:25.172
It will do a number on you.

18:25.206 --> 18:28.689
Live or die. Make your choice.

18:31.896 --> 18:33.758
-I-I choose live.

18:33.793 --> 18:35.655
-Yeah.
-If it's a choice, right?

18:35.689 --> 18:38.000
-Yeah, d-def -- We choose live.

18:38.034 --> 18:39.448
-We got Bert, guys.
We're gonna --

18:39.482 --> 18:41.862
I think we'll be okay.
-Wait, this is a prank.

18:41.896 --> 18:43.206
You all knew Chad.

18:43.241 --> 18:45.310
He wasn't smart enough
to do any of this.

18:45.344 --> 18:48.586
-Oi, when it comes to brains,
Chad is the dog's bollocks.

18:48.620 --> 18:51.068
-M-Maybe it's like an
escape room or something.

18:51.103 --> 18:53.517
-I did one of those once
on vacation.

18:53.551 --> 18:55.241
-It's an escape room.

18:55.275 --> 18:57.379
How fun. I love escape rooms.

18:57.413 --> 19:00.862
The key is we have to work
together as a team.

19:00.896 --> 19:02.206
I'll be project manager.

19:02.241 --> 19:04.068
I think we should split up
into small groups

19:04.103 --> 19:05.482
and each take a section
of the room.

19:05.517 --> 19:07.793
That way, we can
cover more ground.

19:07.827 --> 19:09.413
-Uh, I did one of these once,

19:09.448 --> 19:11.275
and the key was hidden
in my shoe.

19:11.310 --> 19:12.551
-Oi!

19:12.586 --> 19:14.517
-I mean, maybe there's
a trap door or something.

19:14.551 --> 19:17.689
-Oh, great thinking.
Okay, let's split up.

19:17.724 --> 19:22.068
You come with me.
You're a key fixture here, okay?

19:22.103 --> 19:23.724
Don't let anyone
tell you otherwi--

19:23.758 --> 19:25.827
[Retching]

19:25.862 --> 19:28.448
-Oh.

19:28.482 --> 19:31.793
Oh, my God. Are you --
Are you okay?

19:31.827 --> 19:34.724
-Oh, my God. Are youokay?

19:34.758 --> 19:36.379
-Aah! Aah! My arm!

19:36.413 --> 19:38.827
-Holy shit.
-You barfed my arm off!

19:38.862 --> 19:40.620
Aaaah!

19:40.655 --> 19:42.620
-I think this might be real.

19:42.655 --> 19:46.965
-[Straining] It's just those
damn enchiladas.

19:47.000 --> 19:49.655
-Oh, I got to take a Brad Pitt.

19:49.689 --> 19:50.931
-What?

19:50.965 --> 19:53.620
-[Groans]

19:53.655 --> 19:57.206
-[Retching]

19:57.241 --> 20:05.793
♪♪

20:05.827 --> 20:14.586
♪♪

20:14.620 --> 20:18.034
-What are you doing?

20:18.068 --> 20:23.068
-I'll never let
anything happen to you.

20:23.103 --> 20:27.655
I love you.

20:27.689 --> 20:30.103
-[Breathes shakily]

20:34.586 --> 20:37.137
Is this real?

20:38.586 --> 20:41.241
-You bet, baby.

20:45.517 --> 20:47.275
-Oh.

20:50.413 --> 20:53.758
Holy shit.

20:55.586 --> 20:57.379
Oh, no.

21:02.551 --> 21:04.517
-[Screams]

21:04.551 --> 21:10.655
-Nooooooo!

21:10.689 --> 21:13.241
-Aaaaah!

21:16.206 --> 21:18.068
Oh, no, Bert. No, no, no.

21:18.103 --> 21:20.862
This doesn't look good
for you, man.

21:20.896 --> 21:23.931
-I'll make it.
-You -- Are you sure?

21:23.965 --> 21:26.379
It's, like, really bad.
It looks bad.

21:26.413 --> 21:30.310
-You'll be okay, too.
-How can you say that?

21:30.344 --> 21:32.275
You're the one
that makes me okay.

21:32.310 --> 21:35.413
You're the one that makes me
okay, Bert. You're my rock.

21:35.448 --> 21:37.103
-Kameron!

21:37.137 --> 21:38.620
Look at me!

21:38.655 --> 21:42.551
You always had it in you.
You can do this.

21:42.586 --> 21:45.793
I believe in you.

21:45.827 --> 21:48.413
-Really?

21:48.448 --> 21:50.793
Really?

21:50.827 --> 21:53.413
Yeah.

21:53.448 --> 21:54.931
Yeah.

21:54.965 --> 21:58.000
[Retching]

22:04.586 --> 22:07.137
-Everyone remain calm.

22:07.172 --> 22:09.275
We just need to --

22:09.310 --> 22:11.862
[Retches]

22:11.896 --> 22:13.586
This really hurts.

22:16.206 --> 22:18.068
-What are the odds?

22:18.103 --> 22:19.517
-Oh!
-Oh, oh.

22:19.551 --> 22:21.275
-Guess they're finally
together now.

22:21.310 --> 22:23.931
-Bert, this is your fault,
in a way. I hold you acc--

22:23.965 --> 22:25.689
Oh, what's that?

22:25.724 --> 22:29.103
[Machine whirring]

22:29.137 --> 22:33.620
-Holy shit.
It's a beer-pong table.

22:33.655 --> 22:44.241
♪♪

22:44.275 --> 22:54.689
♪♪

22:54.724 --> 22:55.931
[Ball clatters]

22:55.965 --> 22:58.965
-I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

22:59.000 --> 23:01.586
It's about the numbers.

23:01.620 --> 23:03.379
-The Benjamins.
-What?

23:03.413 --> 23:06.448
No, the -- the creepy hooded guy
in the video said

23:06.482 --> 23:09.310
that the poison
would do a numberon us.

23:09.344 --> 23:12.241
There are numbers
on the sides of the cups.

23:12.275 --> 23:14.000
-Okay, so we take the antidote,

23:14.034 --> 23:16.000
we put it in the cups,
and we drink it.

23:16.034 --> 23:17.965
-In the correct cup
and you're fine,

23:18.000 --> 23:19.689
but in the wrong cup...

23:19.724 --> 23:22.275
-[Retching]
-[Screaming]

23:33.482 --> 23:36.620
Probably something like that.
-Okay.

23:36.655 --> 23:38.241
-Oi.

23:38.275 --> 23:42.931
So just grab the balls, walk
them over, put them in the cups.

23:42.965 --> 23:45.965
-Force field is
at full strength.

23:46.000 --> 23:49.137
-No good. That's bad.

23:52.724 --> 23:54.586
-What are you doing?

23:54.620 --> 23:59.103
Chad an I used to be quite the
beer-pong team back in college.

24:02.103 --> 24:05.655
But I need a little
liquid courage.

24:05.689 --> 24:08.827
[Belches]

24:08.862 --> 24:10.724
[Belches]

24:10.758 --> 24:12.517
What number?
-Uh...

24:14.586 --> 24:16.413
12.

24:21.137 --> 24:23.172
-[Cries out]

24:23.206 --> 24:25.655
[Uplifting rock music plays]

24:25.689 --> 24:30.137
♪♪

24:30.172 --> 24:32.137
-♪ I'm taking a chance

24:32.172 --> 24:34.172
♪ Risking it all

24:34.206 --> 24:37.310
♪ For the thrill of a moment

24:37.344 --> 24:39.103
♪ I'm taking a stand

24:39.137 --> 24:41.793
♪ You ain't gonna fall

24:41.827 --> 24:44.655
♪ And you've always known it

24:44.689 --> 24:48.310
♪ They're dying to shake you

24:48.344 --> 24:50.827
♪ Trying their best
to break you ♪

24:50.862 --> 24:53.068
♪ And though the going's rough

24:53.103 --> 24:57.310
♪ You're going home as a hero

24:57.344 --> 25:01.206
♪ 'Cause there's thunder
in your heart ♪

25:01.241 --> 25:04.931
♪ Every move is like lightning

25:04.965 --> 25:06.517
♪ There's the power you feel

25:06.551 --> 25:12.068
♪ When you get your taste
of glory ♪

25:12.103 --> 25:15.517
♪ There's a fire gonna start

25:15.551 --> 25:19.172
♪ And you know they're
going under ♪

25:19.206 --> 25:21.103
♪ You can light the dark

25:21.137 --> 25:27.103
♪ When they hear your heart
of thunder ♪

25:27.137 --> 25:29.931
-[Laughs] Still got i!

25:29.965 --> 25:31.793
-Try my hand.

25:33.689 --> 25:38.241
-Well, here's to swimming
with bow-legged women.

25:38.275 --> 25:40.034
Am I right?
-Doesn't hold up.

25:40.068 --> 25:41.482
-Oh, right?

25:41.517 --> 25:44.448
-Um, here. That's you.
And this one's for you.

25:44.482 --> 25:45.724
-Well, here is to --

25:45.758 --> 25:48.896
-No, no, I can just drink.
Let's just drink it.

25:48.931 --> 25:50.517
Oh.

25:50.551 --> 25:54.379
♪♪

25:54.413 --> 25:57.103
[All groaning]

25:59.965 --> 26:01.586
-Are you some kind
of a math whiz?

26:01.620 --> 26:04.379
-No, no, I was --
was Chad's accountant.

26:04.413 --> 26:08.758
But I left to go pursue my
dreams of working with children.

26:08.793 --> 26:11.000
Guess that's --
It's all over now.

26:11.034 --> 26:12.310
-Oh, don't say that.

26:12.344 --> 26:15.931
Were you a teacher?
-Third-base coach.

26:15.965 --> 26:18.482
Kids will never know
when to go home now.

26:18.517 --> 26:20.862
-Well, you really
took charge back there.

26:20.896 --> 26:22.931
I like a man of action.

26:22.965 --> 26:26.689
You can get to third base
with me anytime.

26:26.724 --> 26:29.103
-Oh! Oi.

26:29.137 --> 26:31.965
-Oh, uh, sorry.

26:32.000 --> 26:34.448
-Guys?
-Oh, shit.

26:34.482 --> 26:37.206
[Groaning, coughing]

26:42.793 --> 26:48.034
-♪ Everybody dies in the end

26:48.068 --> 26:50.965
♪ Everybody dies in the end

26:51.000 --> 26:59.551
♪♪

26:59.586 --> 27:07.931
♪♪

27:07.965 --> 27:09.586
-Wasn't that fun?

27:09.620 --> 27:13.379
My favorite is Alex's twist
on that final-girl trope.

27:13.413 --> 27:17.689
And now on to our next
final girl, Miss Daisy.

27:17.724 --> 27:21.413
She's got a killer
that can't stop, won't stop

27:21.448 --> 27:23.586
driving her mad.

27:23.620 --> 27:27.241
[Chuckles]
Get it?

27:27.275 --> 27:28.689
"Driving Miss Daisy."

27:28.724 --> 27:31.482
-Oh, great. Another movie.
-You'll get there.

27:31.517 --> 27:34.689
But this is one of my all-time
favorite sequels.

27:34.724 --> 27:39.413
And sequels are the lifeblood
of the horror genre.

27:39.448 --> 27:41.275
Wink.

27:41.310 --> 27:44.103
So pay close attention
or you might just meet

27:44.137 --> 27:47.827
the same demise
as Miss Daisy yourself.

27:47.862 --> 27:50.103
Mm?

27:50.137 --> 27:52.103
-Daisy? I know Daisy.

27:52.137 --> 27:54.206
I was gonna break up with her.
I swear.

27:54.241 --> 27:56.862
Please. No. Oh, God.
[Knife slashing]

27:56.896 --> 27:58.344
Oh.

27:58.379 --> 28:01.000
Oh, please.
Don't stab me.

28:01.034 --> 28:03.379
Oh. Not the hand.

28:03.413 --> 28:04.620
Not the hand.

28:04.655 --> 28:15.965
♪♪

28:16.000 --> 28:27.620
♪♪

28:27.655 --> 28:29.103
-[Screams]

28:29.137 --> 28:31.241
[Screaming]

28:31.275 --> 28:41.517
♪♪

28:41.551 --> 28:51.655
♪♪

28:51.689 --> 28:53.517
Who is he?

28:55.379 --> 29:00.137
-He is evil incarnate,
conceived in Hell's womb.

29:00.172 --> 29:03.482
Born without a soul, nourished
by the teat of the Devil.

29:03.517 --> 29:08.793
Spanked by Satan himself.
He is the vessel of death.

29:08.827 --> 29:10.103
-[Whimpers]

29:10.137 --> 29:11.931
-My dear Daisy,

29:11.965 --> 29:13.689
he is your --

29:13.724 --> 29:15.551
[Knife slashes]

29:15.586 --> 29:25.137
♪♪

29:25.172 --> 29:26.793
[Gunshot]
-[Gasps]

29:26.827 --> 29:29.931
-Another nightmare?
-Stop the car.

29:29.965 --> 29:31.551
-We're almost to
my sister's place.

29:31.586 --> 29:34.310
-I said stop
the fucking car, Scott.

29:41.689 --> 29:45.827
-Your nightmares always
resurface around the 4th.

29:45.862 --> 29:48.724
You know that.

29:48.758 --> 29:50.241
-This was different.

29:50.275 --> 29:54.965
They're getting more, uh,
intense, more real.

29:55.000 --> 29:58.896
I have to --
I have to go back to the cabin.

29:58.931 --> 30:02.862
In case he comes back.
-Daisy.

30:02.896 --> 30:07.034
It's been over 20 years.

30:07.068 --> 30:10.275
Baby, he's not coming back.

30:10.310 --> 30:12.896
-He always comes back.

30:12.931 --> 30:20.620
♪♪

30:20.655 --> 30:22.413
-Fine.

30:22.448 --> 30:26.896
♪♪

30:26.931 --> 30:28.655
But I'm coming with you.

30:28.689 --> 30:37.793
♪♪

30:37.827 --> 30:46.931
♪♪

30:46.965 --> 30:56.068
♪♪

30:56.103 --> 30:58.068
-We're here.

30:58.103 --> 31:00.517
[Bird cawing]

31:00.551 --> 31:07.931
♪♪

31:07.965 --> 31:15.517
♪♪

31:15.551 --> 31:18.068
Wait.

31:18.103 --> 31:19.793
Be right back.

31:19.827 --> 31:30.827
♪♪

31:30.862 --> 31:41.931
♪♪

31:41.965 --> 31:52.931
♪♪

31:52.965 --> 32:03.965
♪♪

32:04.000 --> 32:15.241
♪♪

32:15.275 --> 32:26.275
♪♪

32:26.310 --> 32:28.172
-Daisy.

32:28.206 --> 32:30.517
My dear Daisy,
I knew you'd come.

32:30.551 --> 32:37.103
♪♪

32:37.137 --> 32:39.448
-Dr. Castle.

32:39.482 --> 32:41.413
You're alive.

32:41.448 --> 32:42.965
-Do you...

32:43.000 --> 32:45.448
know this guy?

32:45.482 --> 32:47.793
-Daisy.
Thank God you're here.

32:47.827 --> 32:51.448
I must reveal to you,
finally, the terrible truth.

32:51.482 --> 32:53.103
-He is your --

32:53.137 --> 32:55.827
-Brother. I know.

32:55.862 --> 32:58.000
-Oh. Oh, you do.

32:58.034 --> 33:00.241
-Dr. Castle.

33:00.275 --> 33:02.137
How did you know
I would come here tonight?

33:02.172 --> 33:05.620
This cabin and the 4th of July
are deeply interwoven

33:05.655 --> 33:08.655
[Distorted] into the
blood-soaked fabric...

33:08.689 --> 33:12.689
[Taps]

33:12.724 --> 33:15.241
Into the blood-soaked
fabric of the tragic tale

33:15.275 --> 33:17.379
on which you
and your brother is written.

33:17.413 --> 33:19.413
Not only did you come here
as children,

33:19.448 --> 33:21.931
but it is the cursed sight
of the very first night

33:21.965 --> 33:25.103
he came back to enact
his revenge on you.

33:25.137 --> 33:27.206
I remember that fateful day
of Independence

33:27.241 --> 33:30.206
as if it happened
in the fog of a bad dream.

33:30.241 --> 33:32.517
Fireworks going off
across the lake.

33:32.551 --> 33:36.413
Finding your friends' corpses.
Hearing your screams.

33:36.448 --> 33:39.586
Shooting him dozens of times
at point-blank range

33:39.620 --> 33:42.172
only for the bastard
to rise up out of the ashes

33:42.206 --> 33:45.620
[Distorted] and give me this.

33:45.655 --> 33:49.000
Daisy, I came back here for the
same reason that you did.

33:49.034 --> 33:51.689
The inevitability
of Evil's return.

33:51.724 --> 33:53.068
Karma's killer.

33:53.103 --> 33:54.482
Fate's fiend.

33:54.517 --> 33:59.137
Your brother coming back
one last time.

34:01.172 --> 34:03.068
-Who the fuck is this guy?

34:03.103 --> 34:04.482
-After the last time
I killed him,

34:04.517 --> 34:07.931
I buried what
was left out there.

34:07.965 --> 34:10.206
I thought that was
the end of it.

34:11.551 --> 34:16.344
The final kill.
The start of a new beginning.

34:16.379 --> 34:19.241
-Daisy, I'm afraid there's one
more thing I must tell you.

34:19.275 --> 34:21.241
The bond between you
and your brother goes much

34:21.275 --> 34:23.310
deeper than merely the blood
that you share.

34:23.344 --> 34:25.413
-I don't like
where this is going.

34:25.448 --> 34:27.448
-Daisy, you are --

34:28.827 --> 34:30.000
-[Gasps]

34:30.034 --> 34:32.551
-[Mechanical gasping]

34:32.586 --> 34:34.275
[Body thuds]

34:34.310 --> 34:44.344
♪♪

34:44.379 --> 34:45.793
-Oh!

34:45.827 --> 34:52.241
♪♪

34:52.275 --> 34:58.413
♪♪

34:58.448 --> 34:59.931
[Screams]

34:59.965 --> 35:03.241
♪♪

35:03.275 --> 35:06.000
Will?

35:06.034 --> 35:09.689
-I love you, Daisy.

35:09.724 --> 35:11.586
Daisy, shoot him.

35:15.137 --> 35:19.206
-Craaazy night.

35:19.241 --> 35:21.344
-But I watched you die.
-Yeah.

35:21.379 --> 35:24.413
And you didn't shed
a single tear.

35:24.448 --> 35:28.103
You were too busy crying over
your shitty boyfriend, Greg.

35:28.137 --> 35:32.103
-Greg was a good guy.
-Greg was an asshole!

35:32.137 --> 35:35.724
I'm a good guy.
But you never wanted to date me.

35:35.758 --> 35:37.206
I cared about you, Daisy.

35:37.241 --> 35:41.137
-I cared about you, too.
As a friend.

35:41.172 --> 35:43.413
-Don't say that word.

35:43.448 --> 35:44.965
-What word?

35:45.000 --> 35:46.344
Friend?

35:46.379 --> 35:49.310
-I don't want to
just be friends.

35:49.344 --> 35:51.206
I love you.

35:51.241 --> 35:54.413
If I can't have you, no one can.

35:59.586 --> 36:00.931
Come on!

36:00.965 --> 36:12.517
♪♪

36:12.551 --> 36:24.034
♪♪

36:24.068 --> 36:27.241
-[Groans]

36:27.275 --> 36:29.931
Daisy!

36:29.965 --> 36:31.137
You son of a bitch.

36:31.172 --> 36:34.448
You killed your own sister,
my wife.

36:34.482 --> 36:39.379
You. You're just a dream.
Dreams can't hurt you.

36:43.482 --> 36:47.620
I'm not a dead boyfriend.
I'm a dead husband.

36:49.379 --> 36:50.689
[Body thuds]

36:50.724 --> 36:57.448
♪♪

36:57.482 --> 36:59.241
-Oh.

36:59.275 --> 37:01.655
-[High-pitched] That's what I
was trying to tell you,

37:01.689 --> 37:03.034
my dear Daisy.

37:03.068 --> 37:06.172
You are both indestructible.

37:06.206 --> 37:08.965
Two sides of the same coin.

37:09.000 --> 37:11.206
One light, one dark.

37:11.241 --> 37:14.517
Destined to continue
this nightmarish dance

37:14.551 --> 37:19.689
as long as you remain
in opposition.

37:19.724 --> 37:21.482
[Wheezes]

37:25.586 --> 37:27.827
[Neck cracks]

37:27.862 --> 37:36.482
♪♪

37:36.517 --> 37:37.965
-[Roars]

37:38.000 --> 37:40.068
♪♪

37:40.103 --> 37:42.241
[Grunting]

37:42.275 --> 37:52.965
♪♪

37:53.000 --> 38:03.931
♪♪

38:03.965 --> 38:08.172
Tonight is the night
Icome back.

38:12.172 --> 38:16.379
Happy 4th of July, brother.

38:16.413 --> 38:17.689
-Oh?

38:17.724 --> 38:25.965
♪♪

38:26.000 --> 38:28.103
-[Screams]

38:28.137 --> 38:30.793
[Whimpering]

38:32.517 --> 38:35.137
[Fireworks whistling]

38:39.862 --> 38:50.551
♪♪

38:50.586 --> 39:01.275
♪♪

39:01.310 --> 39:11.931
♪♪

39:11.965 --> 39:22.620
♪♪

39:22.655 --> 39:26.896
[Screams]

39:26.931 --> 39:29.206
-Rad Chad loved you
all so dearly.

39:29.241 --> 39:30.620
-Nope.

39:30.655 --> 39:34.724
-But you were so grateful
and so disrespectful.

39:34.758 --> 39:36.620
-Fuck this shit.
-Honey.

39:36.655 --> 39:39.241
-No. We have to figure out
who's doing this to us.

39:39.275 --> 39:41.103
-Well, don't butcher me.

39:41.137 --> 39:43.103
I been across the pond.

39:43.137 --> 39:45.655
-Probably this creepy fuck.

39:47.586 --> 39:50.724
What?
You work at the funeral parlor.

39:50.758 --> 39:52.000
You got to be behind this.

39:52.034 --> 39:55.586
-I'm not.
They just have good benefits.

39:55.620 --> 39:57.379
-I know who it is.

39:59.586 --> 40:01.137
His name is Sam.

40:01.172 --> 40:04.655
He was the only customer
keeping Chad's business afloat.

40:04.689 --> 40:07.448
His ultimate dream was to work
at the video store himself.

40:07.482 --> 40:09.655
But he wasn't, um...

40:09.689 --> 40:11.620
right.

40:11.655 --> 40:13.344
We all thought that he died
when he took an ax

40:13.379 --> 40:16.586
to the stomach
and all of his intestines...

40:16.620 --> 40:18.448
-Owie!
-Come on.

40:18.482 --> 40:20.655
There's no way
anybody could survive that.

40:23.034 --> 40:26.068
-You can't kill pure evil.

40:26.103 --> 40:28.413
[Slow clapping]

40:28.448 --> 40:35.344
♪♪

40:35.379 --> 40:42.000
♪♪

40:42.034 --> 40:44.206
-How are you here?

40:44.241 --> 40:47.379
-Oh, I've been here
the entire time.

40:47.413 --> 40:49.931
You just haven't looked
closely enough.

40:49.965 --> 41:01.275
♪♪

41:01.310 --> 41:03.827
-He double-dipped a chip!

41:03.862 --> 41:06.137
He's an animal.

41:06.172 --> 41:08.206
-So here you all are.

41:08.241 --> 41:13.034
At my best friend's funeral.
But why?

41:13.068 --> 41:15.172
None of you appreciated
the Horror Emporium.

41:15.206 --> 41:17.620
-Huh?
-The what? What?

41:17.655 --> 41:20.620
Rad Chad's Horror Emporium.

41:20.655 --> 41:21.896
-Never heard of it.

41:21.931 --> 41:26.448
-No.
-His masterpiece?

41:26.482 --> 41:30.103
-His gift to this wretched world
that you all let go to waste.

41:30.137 --> 41:32.655
-It was a video store.

41:32.689 --> 41:35.137
I kept telling him,
brick-and-mortar is dead.

41:35.172 --> 41:36.448
-Especially in this economy.

41:36.482 --> 41:37.965
-It's just a bunch
of dumb B-movies.

41:38.000 --> 41:40.413
-Silence!

41:40.448 --> 41:44.482
Okay. This is the shit
that I'm talking about.

41:44.517 --> 41:49.724
You never appreciated Chad,
and you don't appreciate horror.

41:49.758 --> 41:51.482
Not you all.

41:51.517 --> 41:53.241
Noooo!

41:53.275 --> 41:54.931
You don't even know
your own privilege.

41:54.965 --> 41:58.000
-You're a straight white dude
who lives at home with his mom.

41:58.034 --> 41:59.793
-I am a disabled,
straight white dude

41:59.827 --> 42:02.931
who lives at home with his
meemaw, thank you very much.

42:02.965 --> 42:04.206
You're discriminating
against me.

42:04.241 --> 42:06.034
-She didn't discriminate
against you.

42:06.068 --> 42:08.724
She just pointed out --
-Facts.

42:08.758 --> 42:10.034
-Yeah.
-Okay.

42:10.068 --> 42:13.517
Just shut up! Just shut up!

42:13.551 --> 42:15.310
Jesus.

42:15.344 --> 42:18.241
It is time
to play a little game.

42:18.275 --> 42:26.655
♪♪

42:26.689 --> 42:34.931
♪♪

42:34.965 --> 42:43.517
♪♪

42:43.551 --> 42:46.586
-[Groaning]

42:48.689 --> 42:50.103
[Groans]

42:50.137 --> 42:51.793
No, I don't like this.

42:51.827 --> 42:57.137
-And once again, you failed
to take horror seriously.

42:57.172 --> 42:59.172
You mocked. You laughed.

42:59.206 --> 43:01.931
You called horror a B-movie.

43:01.965 --> 43:04.862
Well, the real horror
is the 10,000 bees

43:04.896 --> 43:07.413
that I just put inside of you.

43:07.448 --> 43:10.620
Can you be like Daisy
and pull back the masks

43:10.655 --> 43:14.827
that you hide behind
to reveal your true selves,

43:14.862 --> 43:17.275
or will you be ravaged
from the insides

43:17.310 --> 43:20.689
by a swarm of angry bees?

43:20.724 --> 43:22.068
Time to get busy.

43:22.103 --> 43:24.448
The choice is yours.

43:24.482 --> 43:27.620
"X" marks the spot.

43:27.655 --> 43:29.241
-I mean, he didn't --

43:29.275 --> 43:31.206
he couldn't have put
bees inside of us.

43:31.241 --> 43:33.241
-Well, we were
pretty mean to him.

43:33.275 --> 43:36.344
-You do catch more bees
with honey than with vinegar.

43:36.379 --> 43:39.793
-It's not bees. It's flies.
-A bee just came out of you.

43:39.827 --> 43:41.137
-A bee just came out
of your arm.

43:41.172 --> 43:43.344
-Oh, there are bees!
-Oh, my God!

43:43.379 --> 43:45.000
-Oh, God.
-The bees are real.

43:45.034 --> 43:46.344
The bees are real!

43:46.379 --> 43:47.827
-Okay, okay.
What do we know about bees?

43:47.862 --> 43:50.000
What do we know about bees?

43:50.034 --> 43:51.379
-"Time to get busy."

43:51.413 --> 43:55.000
Busy as a bee.
We -- We have to keep moving.

43:55.034 --> 43:56.586
-I don't think
that's how this works.

43:56.620 --> 43:58.068
-Yeah. No, no, no, no.

43:58.103 --> 44:01.172
If you stop dancing,
the bees start stinging.

44:01.206 --> 44:02.931
So-- Someone give me a beat.

44:02.965 --> 44:04.793
-[Beatboxing]

44:04.827 --> 44:07.379
-Yes.

44:07.413 --> 44:10.655
-What are you guys doing?
Come on, you need to focus.

44:10.689 --> 44:12.103
-Maybe we could sweep 'em out.

44:12.137 --> 44:14.689
-What?
-You know, like a chimney sweep.

44:14.724 --> 44:18.103
-That's still a thing?
-It's coming back in a big way.

44:18.137 --> 44:20.793
Big chimney tried to push
us little guys out,

44:20.827 --> 44:23.344
but chimneys are
recession-proof.

44:23.379 --> 44:25.482
You should check out
my OnlyFans.

44:25.517 --> 44:27.965
Boasts big chimneys.

44:28.000 --> 44:30.724
[Choking]

44:32.862 --> 44:35.724
The bees!
I don't want to die!

44:35.758 --> 44:38.103
[Shouting]

44:40.689 --> 44:43.172
[Bees buzzing]

44:46.482 --> 44:48.793
-Hey, guys,
I think it's working.

44:48.827 --> 44:50.379
I think it's working.

44:52.034 --> 44:53.482
-Take off our masks?

44:53.517 --> 44:57.862
In the movie,
the mask was in the dresser.

44:57.896 --> 45:01.275
"X" marks the spot.

45:01.310 --> 45:03.137
Come get your goddamn keys.

45:03.172 --> 45:05.517
-That makes sense.

45:09.448 --> 45:16.931
♪♪

45:16.965 --> 45:24.689
♪♪

45:24.724 --> 45:27.206
-It's cinnamon.

45:27.241 --> 45:30.758
-I use it in my garden.
It kills bees.

45:30.793 --> 45:32.379
-Oh.

45:32.413 --> 45:36.103
Since I moved to the city,
I can't have a garden anymore.

45:36.137 --> 45:37.862
-It's relaxing.

45:37.896 --> 45:39.448
I work for a nonprofit
that teaches

45:39.482 --> 45:41.241
inner-city children
how to garden.

45:41.275 --> 45:43.931
-Oh, that's nice. Ow!
-Okay. Fuck, no.

45:43.965 --> 45:46.551
Have you guys not seen YouTube?
The Cinnamon Challenge?

45:46.586 --> 45:47.931
That shit'll kill us.

45:47.965 --> 45:49.793
-You guys, I don't think
the dancing worked.

45:49.827 --> 45:52.275
I think it just made them angry.
Ow!

45:52.310 --> 45:54.758
One just stung my kidney.

45:54.793 --> 45:57.517
-We don't have a choice.
-[Groans]

46:01.448 --> 46:03.448
-[Grunts]

46:08.724 --> 46:17.655
♪♪

46:17.689 --> 46:26.103
♪♪

46:26.137 --> 46:29.034
[All coughing]

46:31.137 --> 46:33.068
[Spoon clatters]

46:36.793 --> 46:40.344
-We made a huge mistake.
We should've chosen the bees.

46:40.379 --> 46:43.827
We should've chosen the bees!
[Screams]

46:43.862 --> 46:45.620
-[Screams]

46:45.655 --> 46:47.551
[Coughs]

46:47.586 --> 46:55.896
♪♪

46:55.931 --> 46:57.620
-What are you doing?

46:57.655 --> 47:01.000
-It's too late for me.

47:01.034 --> 47:04.758
-No, you still have time.
-I'm allergic to bees.

47:07.758 --> 47:09.517
Hey, um, I'm --

47:09.551 --> 47:11.068
[Coughs]

47:11.103 --> 47:14.344
I'm really sorry about
what I said about you earlier.

47:14.379 --> 47:17.655
That really wasn't cool.
-It's okay.

47:17.689 --> 47:19.275
I'm different.

47:19.310 --> 47:22.275
But we're all different,
aren't we?

47:22.310 --> 47:26.620
And that is what
makes us special.

47:26.655 --> 47:29.379
-That's so beautiful.

47:33.275 --> 47:34.344
-Oh, God.

47:34.379 --> 47:37.586
-And it's time for you all
to move on

47:37.620 --> 47:39.793
and live your special lives.

47:41.965 --> 47:43.793
-God dang.
-Again?

47:43.827 --> 47:46.034
-God.
-Seriously?

47:47.862 --> 47:49.655
-Oh, God.

47:49.689 --> 47:56.931
♪♪

47:56.965 --> 47:59.241
[Bee buzzing]

48:01.000 --> 48:03.241
[Chains clinking]

48:03.275 --> 48:08.068
♪♪

48:08.103 --> 48:10.000
-What the fuck are you
talking about, fungible?

48:10.034 --> 48:12.241
-What the fuck does
fungible mean?

48:16.827 --> 48:19.379
-Oh. I didn't see you there.

48:19.413 --> 48:22.241
I was just reading
about Papa's big comeback.

48:22.275 --> 48:26.448
Anywho, that last film
was a real doozy, wasn't it?

48:26.482 --> 48:28.896
But now we have
a spooky treat from

48:28.931 --> 48:30.724
[English accent]
across the pond.

48:30.758 --> 48:34.379
[Normal voice] It was an early
Rad Chad's Rad Recommendation.

48:34.413 --> 48:37.931
So sit back
and hold on to your butts.

48:37.965 --> 48:48.241
♪♪

48:48.275 --> 48:51.034
-His instructions said,
"We want mental openness."

48:51.068 --> 48:52.310
I probably shouldn't
have done that.

48:52.344 --> 48:53.931
-The curious cat gets the cream.

48:53.965 --> 48:56.137
-Oh, I'm not sure
that's how that goes.

48:56.172 --> 48:57.413
-There he is.

48:57.448 --> 48:59.103
-What am I meant
to be looking at here?

48:59.137 --> 49:01.344
-I see it, in the curtains.
-What the hell is that?

49:01.379 --> 49:03.172
-It's the "Three Men
and a Baby" ghost.

49:03.206 --> 49:05.724
-That's a cardboard cutout
of a kid.

49:05.758 --> 49:08.275
-Open your minds, guys.

49:08.310 --> 49:09.793
[Camera shutter clicks]

49:09.827 --> 49:12.310
-This is why you've woken me up
at 5:00 a.m. today?

49:12.344 --> 49:14.344
-Apparently, the kid
of one of the crew was

49:14.379 --> 49:16.413
messing around on set
and then...

49:16.448 --> 49:20.827
He fell out of the window
and landed on some prop swords.

49:20.862 --> 49:22.344
They tried to cover it up,

49:22.379 --> 49:24.344
but that just made
the ghost kid angry.

49:24.379 --> 49:26.000
-Why were there swords
on the set of

49:26.034 --> 49:27.379
"Three Men and a Baby"?

49:27.413 --> 49:30.379
-Open your mind, Rachel.
-It's open. It's open.

49:30.413 --> 49:32.586
-My mum always says
if you open your mind too much,

49:32.620 --> 49:33.931
you let the bats in.

49:33.965 --> 49:35.413
Squawk!

49:35.448 --> 49:38.758
-Some people say that you can
see a shotgun in his hand

49:38.793 --> 49:40.275
because he shot himself.

49:40.310 --> 49:42.724
-So a little kid committed
suicide on a film set?

49:42.758 --> 49:44.586
-Yeah.
-Grim.

49:44.620 --> 49:48.551
-And he's showing you the gun.
He's showing you how he did it.

49:48.586 --> 49:50.896
-Oh, I think they knew
how he did it based on there

49:50.931 --> 49:53.310
being a gunshot wound
in his head.

49:53.344 --> 49:58.413
-So did he fall out of the
window or did he shoot himself?

49:58.448 --> 50:00.586
-It says here it's just
Ted Danson in a tuxedo

50:00.620 --> 50:02.862
doing a dog-food commercial.

50:02.896 --> 50:04.137
-In a tuxedo?

50:04.172 --> 50:06.517
-You know, for fancy dogs.

50:06.551 --> 50:15.344
♪♪

50:15.379 --> 50:16.793
[Shouts]

50:16.827 --> 50:23.793
♪♪

50:23.827 --> 50:30.620
♪♪

50:30.655 --> 50:33.172
-Thanks for helping me pack
all my brother's stuff.

50:33.206 --> 50:36.310
-You know we wouldn't
let you do this alone.

50:36.344 --> 50:39.413
Have you ever seen
"Three Men and a Baby"?

50:39.448 --> 50:42.620
-No.
-Come on. It's Ted Danson.

50:42.655 --> 50:44.206
Ted Danson.

50:44.241 --> 50:48.413
You know Ted Danson, right?
-Who the fuck is Ted Danson?

50:48.448 --> 50:51.000
-Well, I guess
the song is wrong.

50:51.034 --> 50:54.000
Everybody doesn'tknow his name.

50:55.517 --> 50:57.724
Why did your brother live in
a lighthouse again?

50:57.758 --> 50:59.034
-Everyone always
used to tell him

50:59.068 --> 51:00.689
that his head was
in the clouds,

51:00.724 --> 51:03.931
so I guess this was his way
of living up to the expectation.

51:03.965 --> 51:06.655
-I see what you did there.
-Cheers.

51:06.689 --> 51:07.965
-Oh.

51:08.000 --> 51:15.965
♪♪

51:16.000 --> 51:23.965
♪♪

51:24.000 --> 51:26.448
-Zoe, can I have this?

51:28.724 --> 51:30.517
-Are you okay?

51:32.965 --> 51:34.931
Are you sure you want to
stay here tonight?

51:34.965 --> 51:40.172
-Yeah. Yeah. I'm just puzzled
why he wanted me to have this.

51:41.586 --> 51:44.827
-Is that the one thing he said
he wanted you to have?

51:44.862 --> 51:46.275
-Kind of.

51:46.310 --> 51:48.965
It's more like he wanted me
to take care of it

51:49.000 --> 51:51.275
but not watch it.

51:53.000 --> 51:56.379
My brother was into some
really weird shit.

51:56.413 --> 51:58.000
-Whoo!

51:58.034 --> 51:59.827
I found the remote.

51:59.862 --> 52:05.448
♪♪

52:05.482 --> 52:06.931
-Oh, that's better.

52:06.965 --> 52:10.241
Oh, my God. It's scarier
when it's ginormous.

52:10.275 --> 52:13.689
-Is it just me or does he have
tentacles for arms?

52:13.724 --> 52:15.000
-It's you.

52:15.034 --> 52:16.551
I think that's just
a shadow, Zoe.

52:16.586 --> 52:19.344
I mean, we just want to see
what we want to see.

52:19.379 --> 52:22.068
-No, look closer.
-Yeah. It's not tentacles.

52:22.103 --> 52:25.275
It looks more like blades
for arms.

52:25.310 --> 52:28.068
-But why would a boy
who either fell out of a window

52:28.103 --> 52:31.655
or shot himself come back
a super-sword man?

52:34.206 --> 52:37.413
[Camera shutter clicking]

52:40.689 --> 52:42.379
What?

52:42.413 --> 52:49.862
♪♪

52:49.896 --> 52:52.413
[Fly buzzing]

52:52.448 --> 52:59.827
♪♪

52:59.862 --> 53:01.551
[Screams]

53:01.586 --> 53:08.517
♪♪

53:08.551 --> 53:10.379
What?

53:12.068 --> 53:14.482
-I'm sleeping with you tonight,
Rachel.

53:14.517 --> 53:16.793
-I'll wear my best
pajamas for you.

53:16.827 --> 53:18.655
-Do you want to go?

53:18.689 --> 53:27.931
♪♪

53:27.965 --> 53:37.172
♪♪

53:37.206 --> 53:39.206
-These are your best pajamas?

53:39.241 --> 53:42.241
-I hope you brought earplugs
'cause I snore like a kaiju.

53:42.275 --> 53:50.000
♪♪

53:50.034 --> 53:52.241
-Why did you
want me to see this?

53:52.275 --> 54:01.655
♪♪

54:01.689 --> 54:10.931
♪♪

54:10.965 --> 54:20.517
♪♪

54:20.551 --> 54:22.517
[Gunshots]

54:22.551 --> 54:24.517
♪♪

54:24.551 --> 54:27.413
-[Snoring]

54:27.448 --> 54:37.827
♪♪

54:37.862 --> 54:48.517
♪♪

54:48.551 --> 54:58.965
♪♪

54:59.000 --> 55:00.655
-Aah!

55:00.689 --> 55:09.482
♪♪

55:09.517 --> 55:18.034
♪♪

55:18.068 --> 55:21.655
[Screaming]

55:21.689 --> 55:29.413
♪♪

55:29.448 --> 55:37.137
♪♪

55:37.172 --> 55:40.379
-It was sword man.

55:40.413 --> 55:44.862
♪♪

55:44.896 --> 55:47.034
-[Screams]

55:49.724 --> 55:51.206
Huh?

55:51.241 --> 55:59.241
♪♪

55:59.275 --> 56:01.275
-[Screams]
[Glass shatters]

56:01.310 --> 56:11.793
♪♪

56:11.827 --> 56:13.551
What the fuck?!

56:17.793 --> 56:20.724
-Come on.
Fuck, fuck, fuck.

56:20.758 --> 56:22.793
Fuck, fuck, fuck.
Come on.

56:22.827 --> 56:29.206
♪♪

56:29.241 --> 56:31.655
-Not again?
-No!

56:31.689 --> 56:40.551
♪♪

56:40.586 --> 56:49.551
♪♪

56:49.586 --> 56:58.551
♪♪

56:58.586 --> 57:00.655
-[Growling]

57:00.689 --> 57:11.655
♪♪

57:11.689 --> 57:14.689
[Screaming]

57:14.724 --> 57:23.379
♪♪

57:23.413 --> 57:31.931
♪♪

57:31.965 --> 57:40.689
♪♪

57:40.724 --> 57:49.448
♪♪

57:49.482 --> 57:51.655
[Door hinges creak]

57:51.689 --> 57:58.275
♪♪

57:58.310 --> 58:04.758
♪♪

58:04.793 --> 58:07.103
-Shit. God damn it.
Fucking Jesus.

58:07.137 --> 58:09.137
Sorry, guys.
That got away from me there.

58:09.172 --> 58:10.448
That was -- That was
unprofessional.

58:10.482 --> 58:13.517
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
I don't like this.

58:13.551 --> 58:15.655
Okay, so he's
the mean, sinister type.

58:18.448 --> 58:19.896
[Coughs]

58:19.931 --> 58:21.689
Now let's play a game.

58:23.586 --> 58:25.896
-Gonna name your dog Chalupa?
[Laugh track]

58:25.931 --> 58:27.344
-Other aerosols suck.

58:27.379 --> 58:29.965
-Every night is movie night.

58:30.000 --> 58:36.931
♪♪

58:36.965 --> 58:38.344
-They're tropes.

58:38.379 --> 58:41.689
So here's your apple martini
and your trope,

58:41.724 --> 58:43.241
Mr. Horror Dude.

58:43.275 --> 58:46.241
Welcome to prime time, bitch.

58:46.275 --> 58:57.620
♪♪

58:57.655 --> 58:59.551
-[Grunting]

59:02.413 --> 59:05.241
[Screams]

59:05.275 --> 59:07.034
[Exhales]

59:09.310 --> 59:11.344
It's time.

59:11.379 --> 59:13.896
Your journey has reached
a new threshold.

59:13.931 --> 59:15.655
And now...

59:15.689 --> 59:17.344
[Metal squeaking]

59:17.379 --> 59:19.827
Excuse me.

59:19.862 --> 59:21.586
Okay.

59:21.620 --> 59:23.862
As I was saying...

59:23.896 --> 59:26.206
-So, I'm off the clock?

59:26.241 --> 59:28.724
-Okay, could we just have,
like, a modicum

59:28.758 --> 59:30.551
of professionalism here?

59:30.586 --> 59:32.689
Okay? I mean, what kind of ship
do you think we're running?

59:32.724 --> 59:35.965
-Hey. No, that's on me.
I get you. Let's get back to it.

59:36.000 --> 59:37.689
-Jesus.

59:37.724 --> 59:40.344
Unbelievable.

59:40.379 --> 59:42.689
Okay, as I was saying
before I --

59:42.724 --> 59:45.379
[Metal squeaking]

59:45.413 --> 59:49.448
As I was saying before I was
so rudely interrupted,

59:49.482 --> 59:54.655
it is now time for one of you
to walk the path

59:54.689 --> 59:57.034
less walk-ed.

59:57.068 --> 59:59.344
Not walked a lot or whatever.

59:59.379 --> 1:00:01.827
One of you will take this camera
and venture

1:00:01.862 --> 1:00:07.241
into the depths of horror
not yet known and not yet found,

1:00:07.275 --> 1:00:10.448
although the footage
will be found at a later time.

1:00:10.482 --> 1:00:12.241
Okay. This is really --
I'm fucking this up.

1:00:12.275 --> 1:00:14.448
And it's because
that little fucking freak

1:00:14.482 --> 1:00:16.206
threw me off of my game,
and the TV

1:00:16.241 --> 1:00:17.482
is kind of tugging
on my neck a little bit.

1:00:17.517 --> 1:00:19.413
So let's just get
this over with, okay?

1:00:19.448 --> 1:00:21.931
Go into the darkness and find
the key to release your friends.

1:00:21.965 --> 1:00:23.896
If you succeed,
they will be spared.

1:00:23.931 --> 1:00:25.206
If you fail,

1:00:25.241 --> 1:00:26.620
their skin will be ripped
from their bodies.

1:00:26.655 --> 1:00:30.827
Oh, and whatever you do,
don't stop filming.

1:00:30.862 --> 1:00:38.103
Now, who among you is willing
to make the ultimate sacrifice?

1:00:38.137 --> 1:00:40.137
Choose wisely.

1:00:40.172 --> 1:00:42.068
-I mean, how do we choose?

1:00:42.103 --> 1:00:44.586
-We could Rochambeau.
-Excuse me.

1:00:44.620 --> 1:00:47.275
Bo's dead.

1:00:47.310 --> 1:00:49.310
-I'll do it.
-Like hell you will.

1:00:49.344 --> 1:00:51.379
-Hey, maybe we should do
rock, paper, scissors.

1:00:51.413 --> 1:00:54.172
-Hey, I think
you're a fucking idiot.

1:00:54.206 --> 1:00:57.310
Eenie, meenie, miney, mo.

1:00:57.344 --> 1:01:01.620
Catch a tiger by its toe.

1:01:01.655 --> 1:01:04.931
If he hollers, make him pay
$50 every day.

1:01:04.965 --> 1:01:09.172
And you are...

1:01:09.206 --> 1:01:10.586
it.

1:01:10.620 --> 1:01:11.827
[Laughing]

1:01:11.862 --> 1:01:13.379
-No.

1:01:16.689 --> 1:01:19.551
-Okay, here I am.
-No, no, no.

1:01:19.586 --> 1:01:21.241
You can't do that, Mom.

1:01:21.275 --> 1:01:23.965
-I've dealt with puny men
like him before.

1:01:24.000 --> 1:01:26.517
But look, if something happens,

1:01:26.551 --> 1:01:31.137
I want you to know
I'm fully supportive of...

1:01:31.172 --> 1:01:35.103
